The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, July 7: Jharkhand, Chhattisgarh, Haryana and Tamil Nadu will get Indian Institutes of Management in the first phase of plans to start seven new IIMs, junior HRD minister D. Purandeswari said today.           
	This means Uttarakhand, Jammu and Kashmir and Rajasthan may have to wait longer for IIMs promised to them. Under the XIth five year plan, IIMs were assured to Tamil Nadu, Jharkhand, Uttarakhand, Chattisgarh, Haryana, Jammu and Kashmir and Meghalaya. Of these, an IIM was started in Shillong last year.           
	Earlier this year, in an interim budget speech blooper by Pranab Mukherjee the government unintentionally announced an IIM for Rajasthan too.                   
	 Abuja (PTI): Six crew members of a chemical tanker, including an Indian, have been taken hostage by a militant group in Abuja in Nigeria. Cadet Banjit Singh Dhindsa was on board the Siehem Peace taken hostage on Sunday, a statement issued by the outfit called the Movement for the Emancipation of the Niger Delta, said.                   
	 Ahmedabad (PTI): Seven persons died and five were hospitalised in a serious condition on Tuesday after allegedly drinking illicit liquor in Ahmedabad. The incident sparked protests in the area with women taking to the streets, demanding a crackdown on illegal liquor dens in the state.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): Shiv Sena leader Bal Thackeray underwent an angioplasty on Tuesday in a Mumbai hospital. He could be discharged in two to three days, doctors said. His son Uddhav Thackeray flew in from the US on Monday night.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A gynaecologist who allegedly killed her twin daughters by poisoning them and attempted suicide a week ago in New Delhi has been arrested after her discharge from hospital. Rupa Singh, 35, allegedly poisoned four-year-old Tanya and Twinkle after a fight with her surgeon husband, Rajiv Ranjan.                                                                                                                           
